definition.value: Brachyolmia type 1, Hobaek type is an autosomal recessive form of brachyolmia (see this term), a group of rare genetic skeletal disorders, and is characterized by short stature, short trunk, platyspondyly, horizontal acetabular roof, short femoral neck without corneal opacities.

Brachyolmia type 1, Toledo type is an autosomal recessive form of brachyolmia (see this term), a group of rare genetic skeletal disorders, and is characterized by short stature, short trunk, and platyspondyly, as well as corneal opacities.

Polysyndactyly or PPD4 is a form of preaxial polydactyly of fingers (see this term), a limb malformation syndrome, characterized by the presence of a thumb showing the mildest degree of duplication, being broad, bifid or with radially deviated distal phalanx. Syndactyly of various degrees of third-and-fourth fingers is occasionally present.
